#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:170
msgid "CookiesMiddleware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:177
msgid ""
"This middleware enables working with sites that require cookies, such as "
"those that use sessions. It keeps track of cookies sent by web servers, and "
"send them back on subsequent requests (from that spider), just like web "
"browsers do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:182
msgid "The following settings can be used to configure the cookie middleware:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:184
msgid ":setting:`COOKIES_ENABLED`"
msgstr ":setting:`COOKIES_ENABLED`"

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:185
msgid ":setting:`COOKIES_DEBUG`"
msgstr ":setting:`COOKIES_DEBUG`"

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:190
msgid "Multiple cookie sessions per spider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:194
msgid ""
"There is support for keeping multiple cookie sessions per spider by using "
"the :reqmeta:`cookiejar` Request meta key. By default it uses a single "
"cookie jar (session), but you can pass an identifier to use different ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:198
msgid "For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:200
msgid ""
"for i, url in enumerate(urls):\n"
"    yield scrapy.Request(\"http://www.example.com\", meta={'cookiejar': i},\n"
"        callback=self.parse_page)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:204
msgid ""
"Keep in mind that the :reqmeta:`cookiejar` meta key is not \"sticky\". You "
"need to keep passing it along on subsequent requests. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:207
msgid ""
"def parse_page(self, response):\n"
"    # do some processing\n"
"    return scrapy.Request(\"http://www.example.com/otherpage\",\n"
"        meta={'cookiejar': response.meta['cookiejar']},\n"
"        callback=self.parse_other_page)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:216
msgid "COOKIES_ENABLED"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:218
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:576
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:651
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:691
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:748
msgid "Default: ``True``"
msgstr "預設值：``True``"

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:220
msgid ""
"Whether to enable the cookies middleware. If disabled, no cookies will be "
"sent to web servers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:226
msgid "COOKIES_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:228
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:460
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:509
#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:851
msgid "Default: ``False``"
msgstr "預設值：``False``"

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:230
msgid ""
"If enabled, Scrapy will log all cookies sent in requests (ie. ``Cookie`` "
"header) and all cookies received in responses (ie. ``Set-Cookie`` header)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:233
msgid "Here's an example of a log with :setting:`COOKIES_DEBUG` enabled::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:235
msgid ""
"2011-04-06 14:35:10-0300 [diningcity] INFO: Spider opened\n"
"2011-04-06 14:35:10-0300 [diningcity] DEBUG: Sending cookies to: <GET http://"
"www.diningcity.com/netherlands/index.html>\n"
"        Cookie: clientlanguage_nl=en_EN\n"
"2011-04-06 14:35:14-0300 [diningcity] DEBUG: Received cookies from: <200 "
"http://www.diningcity.com/netherlands/index.html>\n"
"        Set-Cookie: JSESSIONID=B~FA4DC0C496C8762AE4F1A620EAB34F38; Path=/\n"
"        Set-Cookie: ip_isocode=US\n"
"        Set-Cookie: clientlanguage_nl=en_EN; Expires=Thu, 07-Apr-2011 "
"21:21:34 GMT; Path=/\n"
"2011-04-06 14:49:50-0300 [diningcity] DEBUG: Crawled (200) <GET http://www."
"diningcity.com/netherlands/index.html> (referer: None)\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:247
msgid "DefaultHeadersMiddleware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:254
msgid ""
"This middleware sets all default requests headers specified in the :setting:"
"`DEFAULT_REQUEST_HEADERS` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:258
msgid "DownloadTimeoutMiddleware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:265
msgid ""
"This middleware sets the download timeout for requests specified in the :"
"setting:`DOWNLOAD_TIMEOUT` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:269
msgid "HttpAuthMiddleware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:276
msgid ""
"This middleware authenticates all requests generated from certain spiders "
"using `Basic access authentication`_ (aka. HTTP auth)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:279
msgid ""
"To enable HTTP authentication from certain spiders, set the ``http_user`` "
"and ``http_pass`` attributes of those spiders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:282
msgid "Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:284
msgid ""
"from scrapy.contrib.spiders import CrawlSpider\n"
"\n"
"class SomeIntranetSiteSpider(CrawlSpider):\n"
"\n"
"    http_user = 'someuser'\n"
"    http_pass = 'somepass'\n"
"    name = 'intranet.example.com'\n"
"\n"
"    # .. rest of the spider code omitted ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:298
msgid "HttpCacheMiddleware"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:305
msgid ""
"This middleware provides low-level cache to all HTTP requests and responses. "
"It has to be combined with a cache storage backend as well as a cache policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:308
msgid "Scrapy ships with two HTTP cache storage backends:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:310
msgid ":ref:`httpcache-storage-fs`"
msgstr ":ref:`httpcache-storage-fs`"

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:311
msgid ":ref:`httpcache-storage-dbm`"
msgstr ":ref:`httpcache-storage-dbm`"

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:313
msgid ""
"You can change the HTTP cache storage backend with the :setting:"
"`HTTPCACHE_STORAGE` setting. Or you can also implement your own storage "
"backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:316
msgid "Scrapy ships with two HTTP cache policies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/downloader-middleware.rst:318
